$interpreted: Child: Wah! Brother Jia-Shen is amazing!!
Granny Xica: Okie dokie. That's enough for today. Ya'll be careful on the road.
Child: Okay, see you tomorrow Granny Xica. Bye brother turtle~~
Jia-Shen: Told ya'll stinkers a million times, I'm a tortoise, not a turtle.
Granny Xica: You're getting better at performing. Thanks a lot~
Jia-Shen: It's nothing. If Meemaw didn't take me in, I'd have been on the streets long ago. It only makes sense to help out.
Jia-Shen: If I couldn't help out with the entertainment, I'd have to skin off some of my meat to express my thanks~
Granny Xica: Skin off some meat?
Jia-Shen: Everyone knows tortoise is good for the joints~
Granny Xica: Hehe, all you do is make me smile, child~ Alrighty, let's head home.
Granny Xica: It's so noisy up ahead, what's going on? Child, give me a hand and let's go take a look.
Local: If you tear down these houses, where do you expect us to live?
Soldier: Shut it. We're constructing the New City to serve the Snake God and Goddess; you dare disobey?
Local: There's no way the High Priest would let you be so reckless! We want to see the High Priest!
Jia-Shen: (Rats, better get Meemaw outta here before things get rough.)
Jia-Shen: Meemaw, let's get going...
Granny Xica: Excuse me, sir. You can't tear down these houses.
Soldier: Where'd you come from ya old hag? Get outta the way!
Granny Xica: If you tear them down, many people will lose their homes. How could you bear to see these children on the streets?
Granny Xica: What's more, we're attached to everything that's here.
Soldier: They're just a bunch of old crap piles, what the hell are you talking about? Sitting this close to the Holy Shrine, they should've been removed long ago!
Granny Xica: I won't allow you to poke fun of our homes!
Soldier: Oh, yeah!? What're you gonna do, granny?
Jia-Shen: Please, no fighting! If you wanna tear 'em down, just go on ahead! She's just a little fuzz in the head, don't take her too seriously.
Granny Xica: What on god's green earth are you talkin' about, boy!? They will not tear down this house!
Jia-Shen: Meemaw, we'll find another! No use gettin' all battered for this pile of stones and rubble...
Granny Xica: I've lived here half my life. My son, grandchild and husband all left this world before me.
Granny Xica: They're all buried in the backyard...and you want me to up and leave?
Jia-Shen: But...what if you get hurt...?
Granny Xica: Forget it, if you're afraid than I'll do this myself.
Jia-Shen: Meemaw, that's not what I meant...
Granny Xica: If you're adamant about tearing it down, you'll have to get through me first.
Local: Yeah! If you wanna tear 'em down, you'll have to go through me!
Soldier: You think I won't hurt you, old fart? Com' on! Let's do this!
Jia-Shen: Don't you dare touch her!
？？？: What's going on!
Soldier: Forgive me, Captain Humpty, some people are causing a ruckus.
Jia-Shen: (Humpty!? He's just graduated, and he's already a captain!?...So all those connections really do help...)
Humpty: These renovations are to manifest the glory of the Snake God. Anyone who resists is to be arrested for causing civil unrest!
Jia-Shen: (Crap! Can't get in trouble with the army, otherwise, Meemaw and them will all get arrested!)
Local: Hey! That turtle fella is hitting himself!
Granny Xica: Jia-Shen!? What on earth are you doing!?
Jia-Shen: WOAH HO HO! This outstanding young buck looks familiar...
Jia-Shen: Humpty, been a looooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooong time.
Humpty: Eh? Turtle trash?
Jia-Shen: Yes, it's little ol' me. How so splendidly wonderful it is to see you here.
Humpty: Hmph. You live here? If you're trying to mess things up, then get the hell outta the way!
Jia-Shen: No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no! I just wanna help, whatta ya say? Hold off on the construction and I'll  take care of these rabble-rousers.
Jia-Shen: Promise I can make things a whole lot easier for you~
Granny Xica: Jia-Shen, who said we wanted to bargain with them! Get back here!
Jia-Shen: Meemaw, a wise man flows like water, becoming one with his circumstances~you gotta help me on this one~
Local: You coward! Traitor!
Jia-Shen: So what! I may got no guts but us tortoises live a long time, I'll tell you~Humpty, whatta ya say?
Humpty: Hmmm, I see. Makes sense, but...
Humpty: Why do I need to listen to a bunch of untouchables!? Come on, boys, round up everyone who was causing a ruckus!
Jia-Shen: No...!
？？？: Stop!
Humpty: You, what are you doing here!?
Pang: Merely passing by, but I can't stand by and let injustice prevail...
Soldier: Humpty, sir! Are you okay!?
Humpty: Oh, shut it! I got flung this far, you think I'm alright!?
Humpty: I'm w-w-w-warning you, don't you think about coming any closer...
Pang: If you'd like to continue sparring, I'd be honored.
Humpty: ...Damn, retreat!
Humpty: ...I'll give you 3 days!
Humpty: After 3 days I'm tearing 'em all down whether you're living here or not!
